%N A116120 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k-5 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 1.
%C A116120 If k has d digits, the concatenation is k//k-5 = 10^d*k+k-5 = m*(m+1), therefore k//k-7 = 10^d*k+k-7 = (m-1)*(m+2), so there is a large overlap with A116110. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%Y A116120 Cf. A116115, A116121, A116134, A116251.
